frc-docs, the official FIRST documentation for FIRST Robotics Competition, is accepting new translators for the upcoming changes to the 2022 Control System Documentation. Interested applicants can apply at https://transifex.com/wpilib/frc-docs

We had an amazing success during the 2021 season from our translations. We have a couple of statistics available for those who are interested.

frc-docs contains a total of 10.18K strings, for a total of 236K words. We currently support 6 languages (French, Spanish, Chinese, Turkish, Portuguese, and Hebrew). Out of the 6 languages, 4 reached a state of completion over 90%. Over 1 million words between 6 languages combined were translated. This is the equivalent of ~10 dictionaries (average of 140k words per). If teams in affected countries is a measure of impact, then translations have impacted 314 teams (or more) from Spain, Mexico, France, China, Taiwan, and Turkey.

This could not have been possible without our amazing language maintainers, reviewers and translators! Thank you, thank you, thank you.

Individuals wishing to translate can visit: https://transifex.com/wpilib/frc-docs
Individuals wishing to contribute docs content: GitHub - wpilibsuite/frc-docs: Official FRC Documentation powered by Read the Docs
